column1: .@DanFeltesNH has been fighting for working families his entire career - from working as a legal aid lawyer to the state senate and his campaign for governor. I'm deeply grateful for his service and look forward to what comes next. -mwh #nhpolitics
I'm extremely proud to have @ChrisPappasNH as my representative and thrilled to see him re-elected. We need more of his bipartisan problem-solving in Congress. -mwh #nhpolitics

Congratulations to @AnnMcLaneKuster and also a big thank you for your leadership through your Seat at the Table initiative to elect more strong Democratic women leaders across our state! -mwh #nhpolitics

.@JeanneShaheen congrats on your big victory tonight! We've got a lot of work ahead of us in the Senate to help contain this virus and build back better and I look forward to continuing to work with you to deliver results for the people of New Hampshire. -mwh #nhpolitics
Stay. In. Line.   If you get to the polls before closing time you have a right to cast your ballot. So wait it out and stay in line to #vote.
Great energy at the polls from Newfields to Nashua. Haven't voted yet? You're running out of time! Go to https://t.co/TPtqPbGEfm and head to the polls. #nhpolitics https://t.co/iFqm1sUXYy
If you're at the polls and run into problems @NHDems have your back. Call 603-466-8683 to receive voter assistance. https://t.co/VvvOJBtaoU

Over the last days we’ve seen Joe Biden’s deep empathy paired with his ability to make a difference in the lives of everyday Americans. Joe has spent his life dedicated to service and he is the experienced leader that we need as our next President. -mwh https://t.co/0jzRQEoNQc
Brayden you make me proud to be a Granite Stater. Thank you for your courage and for sharing your powerful story with our country today. -mwh https://t.co/9hLPCAZSi9

Incredibly powerful to watch my friend Kamala Harris make history & officially accept the nomination to be Vice President. We joined the Senate together where I have seen her compassion dedication & determination shine through every day. She will be an exceptional VP. -mwh https://t.co/BJsjsQcHgN
